    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>beef mince</strong> to the dish, breaking it up into rough, large chunks and cook for 1-2 min or until very lightly browned all over</p><p>Once browned, stir in 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p>",
