    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Sprinkle in your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add your<strong> beef stock mix </strong>with 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]<strong> </span>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 25 min – this is your <strong>keema aloo</strong></p>",
